properties.areaDesc: Admiralty Inlet; Northern Inland Waters Including The San Juan Islands
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 10 at 3:51PM PST until January 11 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southeasterly winds 15 to 25 kt becoming northerly 15 to
25 knots on Saturday.

* WHERE...Northern Inland Waters Including The San Juan Islands
and Admiralty Inlet.

* WHEN...Until 4 AM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 21 to 33 knots
and/or seas 10 feet or higher are expected to produce hazardous
wave conditions to small craft. Inexperienced mariners,
especially those operating smaller vessels should avoid
navigating in these conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST SATURDAY... ...GALE WARNING WILL EXPIRE AT 4 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON
